## Key Files
- `next.config.ts`: Configuration for Next.js, including internationalization setup
- `tailwind.config.ts`: Configuration for Tailwind CSS styling system
- `src/middleware.ts`: Configuration for middleware that handles routing and internationalization
- `src/i18n/routing.ts`: Configuration for internationalization routing
- `.env`: Environment variables configuration for both development and production
- `messages/en.json` & `messages/pl.json`: Translation message files for English and Polish languages
- `src/app/[locale]/layout.tsx`: Main layout component with locale-specific configuration
- `src/app/components/ui/`: Reusable UI components following the project's design system
- `src/lib/validations/`: Validation schemas for forms and data structures

## Component Structure
- Components are organized by feature and functionality
- UI components are placed in the `src/app/components/ui/` directory
- Page-specific components are placed in their respective page directories
- Animation components are placed in the `src/app/components/motion/` directory
- Shared functionality is implemented in custom hooks in `src/app/hooks/`

## Internationalization 
- The project uses next-intl for internationalization
- Translation keys are organized hierarchically by feature/component
- Locale is determined by the URL route (/en for English, / for Polish)
- Translation files are stored in the `messages/` directory
